TI  - Single-Cell RNA Sequencing Transcriptomics Revealed HCMV IE2-Related Microglia 
      Responses in Alzheimer's-Like Disease in Transgenic Mice.
PG  - 1331-1345
LID - 10.1007/s12035-023-03553-y [doi]
AB  -     Although multiple factors are known to concur with Alzheimer's disease (AD), 
      the relationship between human cytomegalovirus (HCMV) and AD-like disease is 
      unclear. Here, we propose a hypothesis that HCMV immediate-early 2 (IE2) protein 
      promotes microglia activation and thus leads to AD-like disease. We successfully 
      constructed IE2 transgenic mice expressing IE2 in the hippocampus. Single-cell 
      sequencing analysis revealed that IE2 promoted the activation of microglia and 
      upregulated the expression of disease-associated microglia genes. Differentially 
      expressed gene analysis and pathway enrichment revealed that IE2 upregulated 
      immune and nervous system disease-related genes. Immunohistochemical analysis 
      showed that the expressions of both amyloid precursor protein (APP) and p-Tau 
      were significantly upregulated in the brains of IE2 mice and were markers of AD. 
      Taken together, these findings provide useful insights into AD-like disease 
      activated by HCMV IE2.
